abstract: >-
  FCE-M is a prototype implementation of a native morphogenetic memory
  layer that integrates the FCE-Omega (Fragmergent Causal
  Exponentiation with Omega-Coagulation) field-theoretic framework on
  top of UFME (Unified Fragmergent Memory Engine). The system enforces
  a strict architectural separation: UFME manages memory, D_Cortex
  verifies epistemic truth, FCE-Omega measures morphogenetic becoming
  (assimilation, residue, coagulation, reference). The central
  contribution is the explicit distinction between OmegaRecord (the
  irreversible historical fact of coagulation) and ReferenceField (the
  derived functional field that classifies future events
  morphogenetically without overriding epistemic truth). Validated
  through 268 functional and unit tests across five evolution stages
  ending in v0.6.0 Native Memory Prototype.
